[2]
Date: 4 Nov 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: CNN 3 Nov 2001 [edited]
<http://www.cnn.com/2001/US/11/03/inv.anthrax.va/index.html>

Anthrax traces found at Washington VA hospital
--------------------------------------------------------
A mailroom in the Department of Veterans Affairs Medical Center has tested
positive for anthrax [_B. anthracis_], the federal agency reported
Saturday. The mailroom is located in a hospital that houses 250 patients
but is not near patient areas, said Phil Budahn, the VA's media relations
director. But, he added, hospital officials are keeping "a close eye on
patients."
Swabs were taken in the mailroom 30 Oct because the hospital receives its
mail from the main Brentwood branch post office in Washington, the facility
that processed an anthrax-laden letter sent to Senate Majority Leader Tom
Daschle. 2 Brentwood postal employees have died of inhalation anthrax, and
2 others are hospitalized with the same disease.
Of the 22 swabs, one was positive, Budahn said. Administrators closed the
mailroom, he said.
Hospital administrators at present are not considering moving patients,
Budahn said.
